<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-27-0334 </DOCNO><TEXT>Method of coal hydrogenation with semisolid phase hydrogenation followedby gas phase hydrogenation, characterized in that the coal oils fromthe semisolid phase hydrogenation are separated by partial condensationin an intermediate separator under process pressure into a higher-boilingliquid portion and a lower-boiling vapour portion, the vapour portionis conducted through gas phase reactors and is converted to (partly)refined products having a lower boiling range, the liquid portion, whichcontains the largest part of the higher-boiling fractions, is drawn offbefore the gas phase reactor and is supplied as a portion of the solventto the coal slurrying.</TEXT></DOC>